---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Downloads"
  description="Download Emu198x release archives and choose the right per-system emulator binary."
>
  <main class="container downloads" data-pagefind-body>
    <p class="eyebrow">Releases</p>
    <h1>Download Emu198x</h1>

    <section class="intro">
      <p class="lede">
        Emu198x ships per-system binaries through GitHub Releases. Pick the
        archive for the machine and operating system you want, unpack it, then
        run that binary directly.
      </p>
      <div class="actions" data-pagefind-ignore>
        <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/emu198x/emu198x/releases/latest">
          Latest release
        </a>{' '}
        <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/emu198x/emu198x/releases">
          All releases
        </a>{' '}
        <a class="button secondary" href="/docs/getting-started/">
          Getting started
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="download-grid" aria-label="Release contents">
      <article>
        <h2>Released binaries</h2>
        <p>
          The primary release archives are built for the native verifier shells:
        </p>
        <ul class="binary-list">
          <li><code>emu198x-spectrum</code> — ZX Spectrum family</li>
          <li><code>emu198x-c64</code> — Commodore 64</li>
          <li><code>emu198x-amiga</code> — Commodore Amiga</li>
          <li><code>emu198x-dragon</code> — Dragon 32</li>
          <li><code>emu198x-game-boy</code> — Nintendo Game Boy</li>
          <li><code>emu198x-nes</code> — Nintendo NES</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2>Platforms</h2>
        <p>
          Release archives are produced for the current desktop targets:
        </p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Platform</th>
              <th>Target</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>macOS Apple Silicon</td>
              <td><code>aarch64-apple-darwin</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>macOS Intel</td>
              <td><code>x86_64-apple-darwin</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Linux x86_64</td>
              <td><code>x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Windows x86_64</td>
              <td><code>x86_64-pc-windows-msvc</code></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Release commands vs source commands</h2>
      <p>
        The documentation often uses <code>cargo run</code> because the same
        command works from a source checkout. With a release archive, use the
        unpacked binary name instead.
      </p>

      <pre><code># Source checkout form
cargo run --release -p emu198x-nes --no-default-features -- \
  --rom game.nes \
  --frames 300 \
  --screenshot nes.png

# Release archive form
./emu198x-nes --rom game.nes --frames 300 --screenshot nes.png</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>ROMs, firmware, and media</h2>
      <p>
        Emu198x does not ship commercial ROMs, firmware, disks, tapes, or
        cartridges. You provide those yourself from hardware you own or another
        legal source. Some systems can start from a cartridge or disk image;
        others need a local firmware path before they can boot.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Build from source</h2>
      <p>
        Source builds are still the right path for development, unreleased
        changes, and systems outside the primary release set. See the
        {' '}<a href="/docs/getting-started/">getting started guide</a> for source
        checkout examples.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .downloads {
    padding-block: 4rem;
  }

  h1 {
    max-width: 920px;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: clamp(3.2rem, 9vw, 7rem);
    line-height: 0.9;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.1rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
  }

  section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .intro {
    max-width: 860px;
  }

  .lede {
    margin: 1.35rem 0 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.42rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-flex;
    min-height: 44px;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 7px;
    padding: 0 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: white;
  }

  .secondary {
    background: var(--panel);
    color: var(--ink);
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px var(--line-strong);
  }

  .download-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.95fr) minmax(0, 1.05fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .download-grid article {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .binary-list {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .binary-list li {
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
  }

  p,
  li {
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  @media (hover: hover) and (pointer: fine) {
    .primary:hover {
      background: var(--accent-strong);
      color: white;
    }

    .secondary:hover {
      background: var(--paper-strong);
      color: var(--accent-strong);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .download-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
